&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sr. Milk Accounting Specialist&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;em&gt;US&lt;/em&gt; &lt;em&gt;Remote | Full-Time | Exempt&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you know milk accounting — the payrolls, the pooling, the billing, the balancing — and you&#39;re ready to do it at scale across a diverse client portfolio, this role is for you. As a Sr. Milk Accounting Specialist at Ever.Ag, you&#39;ll own the full Producer Payroll, Plant Billing, Milk Purchase, and Pooling processes for multiple clients, serving as their primary point of contact and a key resource across the organization.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This isn&#39;t a role where you do the same thing every day. You&#39;ll be working across 20+ clients, navigating Federal Order regulations, troubleshooting complex payroll issues, and collaborating with producers, labs, field reps, and internal teams to keep everything running accurately and on time. You&#39;ll also serve on our Tier II Payroll Support Team, contributing your expertise to the broader organization.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Execute producer payrolls (on-prem and SaaS) accurately and on schedule for multiple clients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage milk/component weights, data entry, and resolution within our operating systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Validate payments against Federal Order regulations — formulas, pricing, labs, and weights — and maintain audit-ready records&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Complete balancing and plant billing activities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the lead communicator with all parties in the payroll process: producers, assignees, labs, field reps, and managers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with Federal Order Marketing Administrators on behalf of clients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify issues and areas for improvement, research solutions, and document findings&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop SOPs, training materials, and process documentation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute as a Tier II payroll support resource across all company clients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with cross-functional teams — tech, customer service, account management — for problem-solving and troubleshooting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in KPI reporting and client relationship development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Bring&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;8+ years of experience in Federal Order milk pooling and payment processes, milk payroll systems, or an equivalent combination of education and experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s degree in business, finance, accounting, or related field (or equivalent experience)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advanced Excel skills; alphanumeric ten-key of 10K KPH or higher strongly preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical mindset — you can spot patterns in data, trace transactions, and draw sound conclusions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication skills; able to translate complex numerical data for clients, regulators, and internal stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work independently, manage competing deadlines, and adapt when priorities shift&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Availability for on-call support as needed (evenings, weekends, holidays)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why You&#39;ll Love It Here&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Remote work&lt;/strong&gt; — work from anywhere in the U.S.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Variety&lt;/strong&gt; — no two days look the same; you&#39;ll work across clients, processes, and problem types&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Growth&lt;/strong&gt; — we&#39;re a growing team with several long-tenured members approaching retirement. That means real, near-term opportunities to step into leadership and expanded ownership for the right person&lt;/li&gt;
